Package: acspatial
Title: Algorithmic Complexity of Spatial Data
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Jakub", family = "Nowosad", 
      role = c("aut", "cre"),
      email = "nowosad.jakub@gmail.com", 
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1057-3721"))
Description: The algorithmic complexity of spatial data is a measure of the amount of information in a data set. This package provides functions to calculate the algorithmic complexity of spatial raster data using the layered block decomposition method (Rueda-Toicen (2018) <doi:10.5281/zenodo.1291510>).
